------------------------------------------------

**Here is my verify.js**
```javascript
const {run} = require("hardhat");

const verify = async (contract, args) =>{
    const address = contract.address;
    console.log(`Verifying Contract...\t\t\t${address}\t\t${args}`);
    try{
        await run("verify:verify",{
            address: address,
            constructorArguments: args
        });
    }catch(ex){
        if(ex.message.toLowerCase().includes("already verified")){
            console.log("Already Verified");
        }else{
            console.log("Verifying Contract Error\t", ex);
        }
    }
}

module.exports = {
    verify
};
```

### Minimal reproduction steps

1. write a simple contract use solidity
2. write deploy.js
3. write verify.js
4. configure your hardhat.config.js as needed
5. such as me use sepolia test network to deploy my contract
6. run command line: yarn hardhat deploy --network sepolia

**NOTICE: I used "AggregatorV3Interface.sol" to get token price. And I had successed run the same code three days ago.**

